  <summary>2/2/1999--Introduced.
Organ Donor Leave Act -Permits a Federal employee, in any calendar year, to use not to exceed: (1) seven days of paid leave to serve as a bone-marrow donor; and (2) 30 days of paid leave to serve as an organ donor.</summary>
